| Location Type 0 for Stores/Dealers, 1 for Warehouses, 2 for Suppliers | Client sends both warehouse and store inventory data in the inventory.csv file. We seperate these two with sales_channel column. F.col("sales_channel").isin({"ON_TRADE_O", "OFF_TRADE", "OTEL"}) filters Store sales and F.col("sales_channel").isin({"Wholesale"}) filters Warehouse shipment data. Warehouse shipment data is written to operation/sales_wholesale path and Store sales is written to operation/sales path. | Store Sales: https://gitlab.com/invent-analytics/pipeline/meydiageo/-/blob/master/scripts/opal/pre_etl/sales.py Warehouse Shipment: https://gitlab.com/invent-analytics/pipeline/meydiageo/-/blob/master/scripts/opal/pre_etl/sales_wholesale.py |

| Cross Join Cases | Client may not send some product_code or store_code columns since the incoming data may not change based on product or store. These Null columns are imported by cross joining with all product/dealer codes on Invent’s side. product_code column in lead_time.csv table is Null. - S3 Bucket Control

At the start of meydiageo_daily dag` s3://invent-meydiageo/{RUN-DATE}` is checked to see if the files are sent by the customer are available in that path. If not, an email is sent to the mail addresses(both to us and the customer) declared in `meydiageo.yaml`. After sending the fail email, program checks the s3 bucket for 3 hours and if the files are not present in the bucket at the end of 3 hours, another email is sent stating that files are not found.

- Error Alerts in Dags

Dags that trigger errors if an error is found are as follows:

1. meydiageo_daily
2. meydiageo_noob_daily
3. meydiageo_rocket_daily
4. meydiageo_noob_etl
5. meydiageo_noob_weekly
6. meydiageo_pre_etl
